org.itemscript.core.values
Class WeakArray

java.lang.Object
  org.itemscript.core.values.WeakContainer
      org.itemscript.core.values.WeakArray
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Iterable<JsonValue>, java.util.Collection<JsonValue>, java.util.List<JsonValue>, HasSystem, JsonArray, JsonContainer, JsonGetAccess, JsonValue, ToJsonStringWithIndent
public class WeakArray
extends WeakContainer
implements JsonArray, ToJsonStringWithIndent

A WeakArray implements a JsonArray that does not change the state of values contained within it, and whose contents cannot be changed through any of the JsonArray methods. It can be useful when you need something that looks like a JsonArray, but cannot be changed, and whose values may be inside other containers. It should be used with caution, since it does not fully substitute for JsonArray and because the values contained within it may change without notice.

Author:
Jacob Davies
jacob@itemscript.org

a

public JsonArray a(byte[] value)
Description copied from interface: JsonArray
Add a binary value to this array, returning this JsonArray. This method can be used for inline initialization of an array.

Note: The JsonString object will point to the underlying byte[] that was supplied; it will not copy it. The internal operations of the JsonSystem will not change it, but it will be made directly available through the JsonString object's JsonValue.binaryValue() method. So, if you need to make sure that the original is not changed, you must copy it before supplying it to this method.

Specified by:
a in interface JsonArray
Parameters:
value - The binary value to be added.

This JsonArray object.

set

public void set(int index,
                byte[] value)
Description copied from interface: JsonArray
Set a binary value at the given index.

Note: The JsonString object will point to the underlying byte[] that was supplied; it will not copy it. The internal operations of the JsonSystem will not change it, but it will be made directly available through the JsonString object's JsonValue.binaryValue() method. So, if you need to make sure that the original is not changed, you must copy it before supplying it to this method.

Specified by:
set in interface JsonArray
Parameters:
index - The index to set at.
value - The binary value to set.
